<p>I have a simple custom <code>NSObject</code> subclass like this (<code>.m</code> file):</p>  <pre><code>@interface SimplePoint () @property double latitude; @property double longitude; @end </code></pre>  <p>that, if I'm not wrong (correct me if I'm), does not need to implement <code>&lt;NSCopying&gt;</code> protocol.</p>  <p>On the other hand, I have another <code>NSObject</code> subclass with an <code>NSMutableArray</code> intended to contain <code>SimplePoint</code> objects:</p>  <pre><code>@interface Container () @property (strong, nonatomic) NSMutableArray *simplePoints; @end </code></pre>  <p>I need to make copies of <code>Container</code> objects, so I'm adopting the <code>&lt;NSCopying&gt;</code> protocol and implementing the <code>copyWithZone:</code> method, but I'm not sure of which the correct way to do this should be. Maybe this one?:</p>  <pre><code>- (id)copyWithZone:(NSZone *)zone {    id copy = [[[self class] alloc] init];     if (copy) {       NSMutableArray *pointsArray = [[NSMutableArray alloc] init];       for (id item in self.simplePoints) {         if ([item isKindOfClass:[SimplePoint class]]) {             [pointsArray addObject:[(SimplePoint *)item copy]];         }       }       [copy setSimplePoints:pointsArray];   }    return copy; } </code></pre>  <p>Or this one:</p>  <pre><code>- (id)copyWithZone:(NSZone *)zone {    id copy = [[[self class] alloc] init];     if (copy) {       [copy setSimplePoints:[self.simplePoints copy]];    }     return copy; } </code></pre>  <p>Or a different one?</p>  <p>Thanks in advance</p>